If ye pass beyond form, O friends, ’tis Paradise and rose-gardens within
rose-gardens.

When thou hast broken and destroyed thine own form, thou hast learned to break
the form of everything.

After that, thou wilt break every form; like Haydar ('Ali), thou wilt uproot
the gate of Khaybar.
